title: For Sale:  Rock River Arms 20" Predator Pursuit/Magpul PRS/Geiselle G2S-E
postcontent:
Looking to get rid of my AR in the interest of buying a new rifle to replace it. I've just been thinking I'd rather have a bolt action as I enjoy shooting them more than semi-autos. 

I built the lower from a stripped Palmetto State Armory lower, but ordered the complete upper through a dealer directly from Rock River Arms. The RRA upper has the same 20" stainless steel barrel as RRA's National Match rifles. When sold as a complete rifle, RRA guarantees the Predator Pursuit as sub-1 MOA accuracy. I can verify that this rifle is capable of 0.5 MOA when shot from a locked down bench rest, and I can get between 0.75-0.9 MOA 5-shot groups out of this rifle off a bipod using handloads (if I can channel my inner marksman). Occasional groups where I can keep myself in line have been 0.6-0.7 MOA. I can provide targets and load data to support these claims. I have been able to shoot this rifle out to 470yds where I had 5 bowling pins set up. Was able to hit 3/5 pins on the first shot on repeated occasions with low/no wind. Approximately 600-800 rounds fired and is well taken care of. This is an excellent rifle for anyone looking to buy an AR purpose built for magnified optics. 

In the interest of transparency I will disclose that two winters ago the rifle fell off my truck tailgate when I was out coyote hunting and because of that the scope has a small ding in the tube. I have since run a tracking test and can verify there are no issues. The scope tracks well and holds zero. Essentially just a small cosmetic blemish. Armslist will only let me post one photo. More photos can be sent to email. 

Parts list & prices at time of purchase...

          Upper Half:
RRA 20" Predator Pursuit rifle length upper (.223 Wylde chamber, 1:8 twist) - $675, price for same upper has since increased due to RRA adding railed handguard
Nikon M-223 3-12x42mm optic (Nikoplex reticle and "Rapid Action Turret") - $450
Nikon M-223XR 20moa mount - $70
BCM Gunfighter Charging Handle (Large Latch) - $50
          Lower Half:
Magpul PRS Stock (added extended buttpad) - $260
Ergo grip w/Palm shelf - $50
PSA Lower Receiver with parts - $100
Geissele G2S-E two-stage trigger - $190 (has to be felt to be understood...totally worth the price when compared to a mil-spec trigger)

Total invested: $1,845


Asking $1,400 OBO for complete turnkey package and will provide multiple recipes for handloads if interested. 
***Rifle has never seen a handload above recommended Lyman data, and all loads were worked up from 10% below maximum recommended charge with no overpressure issues. 

Willing to separate complete upper w/optic & mount for $850.

If upper gets sold, lower can be sold separately or possibly parted out. WILL NOT sell lower or lower components unless upper has already been sold. Will probably relist lower/lower components if upper sells separately. 

SERIOUS INQUIRIES will be provided cell phone number. Thanks for your interest.
